  "candidate_index": 3,
  "candidate_text": "Kai fills the kettle a second time though it's already full, watching the water rise to the lip and stopping just before it spills\u2014a small, practiced control in a room where the larger thing sits perfectly aligned at the table's edge, untouched. He keeps his back to it while he works, and the working is deliberate: he dries a mug that is already dry, sets it down, picks it up, sets it down again in a slightly different place, as if rearranging the minor objects of the kitchen might constitute a kind of answer to the harbor's pull he can feel even now, cold and specific, somewhere behind his sternum. The letter holds its right angle. He has not looked at it since he set it there, but he knows without looking that the corner is still true, and that knowing is the closest he will let himself come to touching it.",
